# Minecraft Server Infrastructure Platform

A self-hosted Minecraft server running on Ubuntu Server inside a virtualized homelab environment.

The goal of this project is to learn Linux system administration, networking, automation, monitoring, and infrastructure management by deploying and maintaining a real service used by multiple players.

---

## Objectives

- Deploy a Minecraft server on Ubuntu Server
- Secure the server using Linux best practices
- Automate startup with systemd
- Create automated backups
- Monitor server health
- Document the entire deployment process
- Practice Git and GitHub workflows

---

## Current Status

🚧 In Development

Project progress is tracked using GitHub Projects and GitHub Issues.

